JOHANNESBURG, September 5 – A biker died early Thursday morning in a collision with a truck in Meyerton. Shawn Herbst, spokesperson for Netcare 911, said at 06.15 am paramedics responded to reports of a collision along Jim Fouche Road and Donald Road in Bolton Wolf Meyerton. He said reports from the scene indicate that a motorcycle and a bakkie were involved in a collision. “Medics assessed the scene and found that an adult male had sustained fatal injuries and was sadly declared deceased on the scene,” said Herbst. Police are investigating the cause of the fatal crash. – African News Agency (ANA)